Preconditions:
- The input string `s` is not null.
- The input string `s` contains only lowercase alphabets.
- The input integer `k` is a positive integer.

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer representing the length of the longest ideal string.
- The method returns 0 if there is no ideal string in the input string `s`.
- The method returns the length of the input string `s` if it is an ideal string.
- The method returns the length of the longest ideal string found in the input string `s`.